The paper discusses the network topologies of data centers and their reliability and survivability requirements. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the architecture of data centers, which falls under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The analysis of the benefits of different topologies and their specific level of redundancy falls under cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also discusses the Mean Time To Failure, which is a measure of reliability and falls under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.IT (Information Theory).
